&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Android Top Gun Training Certificate Awarding Ceremony&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On behalf of GTUGs, XI’AN GTUG organized an event for local Android developers who have been trained by Android Top Gun Remote Training, with instructors, also senior developers from USA , on August 1, 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This event was held at A 401, Ascendas Innovation Hub, Xi’an Software Park, Xi’an High-tech Zone, there was 10 participants who are developers from different companies while with the same interest in Android developing, and other 5 organizers from Beyondsoft Xi’an. In the meeting, the developers chat with each other and shared their developing experience together, with fruits and snacks prepared by the sponsor BeyondSoft, Xian.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After several hours of communication, most of the developers became very interested in Gtug Event and Beyondsoft, and wish to attend next time and know more friends in software field so that they can share more information and also get relaxed in their spare time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After GTUG events were held successfully for several times, and with the support of sponsor Beyondsoft and the Android developers who are interested in participating GTUG events, the local developers’ community will surely become more and more influential in Xi’an and bring the companies a large talent pool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Held by Xi’an GTUG (Google Technology User Group), the Android Top Gun Training combines two parts: scene lecture by an honored guest David Cao and on-line course by senior Android developers Jian Zhang and Nelson from Silicon Valley, U.S. The course arrangement is the same as Android Top Gun Training in Silicon Valley, U.S. This could be the best chance to know the latest technology and prospect of Android development. There are 50 audience including senior developers from local company, managers and technical directors, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
